The paper discusses symbolic execution techniques, which are primarily used in software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL) research. It also touches upon security (cs.CR) and formal methods (cs.LO) applications of symbolic execution. Finally, symbolic execution is a technique used in formal verification (cs.FL) of software systems, making this category a possible fit as well.
